<H1>Switch-Level Modelling: Examples</H1>
<HR SIZE=3D"4">

<P>This section provides two examples of implementing circuit designs at =

switch-level.
<H2>1. CMOS Inverter</H2><IMG alt=3D"cmos inverter" align=3D"bottom" =
src=3D"http://www.ee.ed.ac.uk/~gerard/Teach/Verilog/me5cds/inv_sw.gif">
<P>The switch-level description has a similar structure to that of the=20
behavioural, functional or gate level codes, as in this example of a =
CMOS=20
inverter:<PRE>// Switch-level description of a CMOS inverter=0A=
=0A=
module inv_sw (out, in);=0A=
   =0A=
   output  out;               // inverter output=0A=
   input   in;                // inverter input=0A=
   =0A=
   supply1 power;             // "power" connected to Vdd=0A=
   supply0 ground;            // "ground" connected to Gnd=0A=
   =0A=
   pmos (out, power, in);     // instantiate pmos switch=0A=
   nmos (out, ground, in);    // instantiate nmos switch=0A=
   =0A=
endmodule=0A=
</PRE>
<P>Connection to the Vdd power supply is made using the <I>supply1</I> =
net,=20
declared as "power". Similarly, the "ground" terminal is connected to =
the=20
<I>supply0</I> net.
<P>Using the <I>pmos</I> and <I>nmos</I> switch-level primitives the =
respective=20
transistors are instantiated, based on the terminology shown in the =
previous=20
section. Note that the instance name is optional, and has been omitted =
in this=20
example.
<P><A=20
href=3D"http://www.ee.ed.ac.uk/~gerard/Teach/Verilog/me5cds/me95chn1.html=
">Stimulus=20
code for inverter</A>
<H2>2. 1-bit 2-1 Multiplexer</H2><IMG alt=3D"2-1 multiplexer" =
align=3D"bottom" =
src=3D"http://www.ee.ed.ac.uk/~gerard/Teach/Verilog/me5cds/mux21_sw.gif">=

<P>This circuit assigns the output <B>out</B> to either inputs =
<B>in1</B> or=20
<B>in2</B> depending on the low or high values of <B>ctrl</B> =
respectively.<PRE>// Switch-level description of a 1-bit 2-1 multiplexer=0A=
// ctrl=3D0, out=3Din1; ctrl=3D1, out=3Din2=0A=
=0A=
module mux21_sw (out, ctrl, in1, in2);=0A=
   =0A=
   output out;                    // mux output=0A=
   input  ctrl, in1, in2;         // mux inputs=0A=
   wire	  w;                      // internal wire=0A=
   =0A=
   inv_sw I1 (w, ctrl);           // instantiate inverter module=0A=
   =0A=
   cmos C1 (out, in1, w, ctrl);   // instantiate cmos switches=0A=
   cmos C2 (out, in2, ctrl, w);=0A=
   =0A=
endmodule=0A=
</PRE>
<P>An inverter is required in the multiplexer circuit, which is =
instantiated=20
from the previously defined module.
<P>Two transmission gates, of instance names C1 and C2, are implemented =
with the=20
<I>cmos</I> statement, in the format <CODE>cmos=20
[instancename]([output],[input],[nmosgate],[pmosgate])</CODE>. Again, =
the=20
instance name is optional.
<P><A=20
href=3D"http://www.ee.ed.ac.uk/~gerard/Teach/Verilog/me5cds/me95chn2.html=
">Stimulus=20
code for multiplexer</A><BR>
